               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Taʾammǝra ʾIyasus “Miracles of Jesus” (fols. 4ra-103vb) 
 I-1)
                     Introduction (fols. 4ra-12va) 
 - On John the Evangelist as the author of
                     the book; on the creation and the fall of the angels (fols. 4ra-7va) 
 -
                     Story of the family of Adam (fols. 7va-12va) 
 I-2) Taʾammǝra ʾIyasus
                     “Miracles of Jesus”: 34 miracles (fols. 12va-103vb)
 
 Additiones
                     1-2.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- The second part of Text I-1 is introduced with the words mǝʿrāf
                        “chapter” and taʾammǝr “miracle” (s. <locus target="#7va">7va</locus>).</note>
                     <note>- Miracles of Text I-2 are introduced with the words mǝʿrāf “chapter”
                        and/or taʾammǝr “miracle”, or nägär “speech”.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
